cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.CR

The paper discusses the use of social media data for forecasting, which falls under the category of social media analytics. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with data biases, noisy data, and lack of generalizable results, which are common issues in data science and machine learning, making cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions natural language processing and sentiment analysis, which are sub-fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), and the potential for using SM data for security and privacy (cs.CR).
